section.div: Having 300$ more per month pays for house keeping and nanny, giving me more time to code.

div.p: I am grateful to even be in a spot where I can ask you to help me do what I love, in the hope that this benefits you just as much. Maybe one day writing and maintaining open source software can be my full-time occupation.
Here is what I am making…

ul.li: gitoxide - all of Git in Rust for comfortable tooling and performance
dua - a tool to gauge disk usage, fast
GitPython - a widely used python library to interact with Git

div.p: A special thanks goes to Josh Triplett, my very first sponsor who started it all.
